Non-Functional Requirements

Non-functional requirements define the quality attributes and performance standards of CookSnap – Smart Recipe Recommendation System Using Grocery Images.

NFR-01: Performance

The system shall respond to user actions such as image upload, ingredient detection, and recipe recommendation within acceptable time limits.

Acceptance Criteria:

Image upload response time ≤ 3 seconds

Ingredient detection and recipe recommendation completed within acceptable processing time

NFR-02: Security

The system shall ensure secure access and protect user data.

Acceptance Criteria:

Secure login for users and administrators

Unauthorized access to system features is prevented

NFR-03: Reliability & Availability

The system shall be available to users with minimal downtime.

Acceptance Criteria:

System availability of at least 99%

Graceful handling of errors and automatic recovery from minor failures

NFR-04: Usability

The system shall be easy to use by all categories of users.

Acceptance Criteria:

Simple and intuitive user interface

Minimal learning effort required for first-time users
